Package com.microsoft.rest.v3.http

Package containing the HTTP abstractions between the AnnotationParser, RestProxy and HTTP client.
  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    HttpClientFactory
    Creates an HttpClient from a Configuration.
    HttpPipelineLogger
    A Logger that can be added to an HttpPipeline.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractHttpPipelineLogger
    An abstract Logger for HttpPipeline RequestPolicies that contains functionality that is common to Loggers.
    BufferedHttpResponse
    HTTP response which will buffer the response's body when/if it is read.
    ContentType
    The different values that commonly used for Content-Type header.
    ContextData
    ContextData offers a means of passing arbitrary data (key-value pairs) to HttpPipeline's policy objects.
    HttpClient
    A generic interface for sending HTTP requests and getting responses.
    HttpClientConfiguration
    The configuration to be applied on a HttpClient.
    HttpHeader
    A single header within a HTTP request or response.
    HttpHeaders
    A collection of headers on an HTTP request or response.
    HttpMethod
    The HTTP request methods.
    HttpPipeline
    The http pipeline.
    HttpPipelineCallContext
    Type representing context local to a single http request and it's response.
    HttpPipelineOptions
    Optional properties that can be used when creating a HttpPipeline.
    HttpRequest
    The outgoing Http request.
    HttpResponse
    The type representing response of HttpRequest.
    NextPolicy
    A type that invokes next policy in the pipeline.
    ProxyOptions
    proxy configuration.
    ReactorNettyClient
    HttpClient that is implemented using reactor-netty.
    Slf4jLogger
    An adapter that delegates logging to an slf4j Logger.
    SystemOutLogger
    A HttpPipeline HttpPipelinePolicy logger that logs to the StdOut/System.out stream.
    UrlBuilder
    A builder class that is used to create URLs.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    HttpPipelineLogLevel
    The different levels of logs from HttpPipeline's policies.
    ProxyOptions.Type
    The type of the proxy.
